Rather they sell the packs for a profit then buy the specific NFTs they want, especially the redeemable ones. The competition comes from "sweeping the floor" in which everyone tries to buy the lowest priced packs to keep the "floor price" from falling below a certain level so they can then sell those packs for a bigger profit. There are also those who wait for the floor sweeping then try to buy the packs as low as possible. Of course there are many people who open their packs to see if they have any redeemable Funko Pop NFTs. It is not usually easy to get a pack on the drop and can also be difficult to snag a pack after market as the floor is continually swept.
behaveopen: They try to accumulate as many packs as possible for the lowest price so as the redemption period nears they can sell those packs for the maximum profit. People also try to keep the after-market price of the redeemable NFTs high to maximize their profit potential.
